---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { BookOpen, Spade, ChartScatter } from 'lucide-astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Home">
		<!-- background circles -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-[300%] pointer-events-none -z-10">
      <div class="absolute top-[5%] right-[10%] w-[600px] h-[600px] rounded-full bg-amber-100 opacity-70"></div>
      <div class="absolute top-[35%] left-[5%] w-[400px] h-[400px] rounded-full bg-orange-100 opacity-60"></div>
      <div class="absolute top-[55%] right-[15%] w-[500px] h-[500px] rounded-full bg-rose-100 opacity-60"></div>
      <div class="absolute top-[70%] left-[20%] w-[360px] h-[360px] rounded-full bg-amber-100 opacity-50"></div>
    </div>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="px-8 py-32 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-5xl md:text-7xl text-stone-400 leading-tight">
        I make things. <br /> Sometimes they work.
      </p>
    </section>

  <main class="max-w-3xl pl-16 md:pl-32 lg:pl-40 pr-6 md:pr-10 py-24">
  
    <!-- Philosophy -->
    <section class="mb-24">
      <p class="text-stone-600 leading-loose">
        "When I encounter something new, my first instinct isn't just to accept it — 
				it's to find what's underneath. The axioms behind the argument. The rule behind the 
				pattern. I'm not sure if that's curiosity or just the way I'm wired."
      </p>
    </section>

		<!-- Background -->
<section class="mb-24">
  <h2 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-8">Background</h2>
  
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
    
    <div class="flex gap-6">
      <span class="text-xs text-stone-400 w-20 pt-1 shrink-0">-2020</span>
      <div>
        <span class="text-stone-800 font-medium">Korea</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Born and raised</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex gap-6">
      <span class="text-xs text-stone-400 w-20 pt-1 shrink-0">2020-2023</span>
      <div>
        <span class="text-stone-800 font-medium">Warsaw</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">American School of Warsaw, IB</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex gap-6">
      <span class="text-xs text-stone-400 w-20 pt-1 shrink-0">2023–2024</span>
      <div>
        <span class="text-stone-800 font-medium">Waterloo</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Honours Mathematics, University of Waterloo</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex gap-6">
      <span class="text-xs text-stone-400 w-20 pt-1 shrink-0">2024–2026</span>
      <div>
        <span class="text-stone-800 font-medium">Army</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Mandatory service for Republic of Korea Army</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex gap-6">
      <span class="text-xs text-stone-400 w-20 pt-1 shrink-0">2026-now</span>
      <div>
        <span class="text-stone-800 font-medium">Waterloo</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-1">Honours Computer Science, co-op, University of Waterloo</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

		<!-- Projects -->
		<section class="mb-24">
			<h2 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-8">Projects</h2>
			
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
				
				<div>
					<div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
						<BookOpen class="w-4 h-4 text-stone-400" />
						<span class="text-stone-800 font-medium">dchup</span>
						<span class="text-xs text-stone-400">TS-React · Python-fastapi · AWS</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
						Built a full-stack flashcard app — my first time touching a real backend, a database, and deployment all at once. Learned more from breaking things than from building them.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
						<Spade class="w-4 h-4 text-stone-400" />
						<span class="text-stone-800 font-medium">Solitaire</span>
						<span class="text-xs text-stone-400">React</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
						Started in Dart, failed, rebuilt in React. Ended up being the project I learned React from. Still play it sometimes.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
						<ChartScatter class="w-4 h-4 text-stone-400" />
						<span class="text-stone-800 font-medium">CxC Hackathon</span>
						<span class="text-xs text-stone-400">Python · pandas · matplotlib</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
						My first hackathon. Analyzed wildfire data with a team over three weeks — learned pandas, matplotlib, and how to present technical work to an audience. Won the MEF Award.
					</p>
				</div>

			</div>
		</section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>